.Dd April 7, 1996
.Dt ZERO 4
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm zero
.Nd the zero device
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
device accepts and reads data as any ordinary (and willing)
file,
but throws away any data written to it, and returns an endless
supply of null bytes when read.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width /dev/zero
.It Pa /dev/zero
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr full 4 ,
.Xr null 4
.Sh HISTORY
A
.Nm
device appeared in
.Bx 4.4 .
